main event: An observed object resembling a planet of first magnitude brilliance traveling in an easterly orbit was reported in the Philippines.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of 25 degrees and moved north at 25 degrees elevation., The sighting lasted for 1.3 minutes and was lost in clouds at 15 degrees elevation., The report suggests the object could possibly be an aircraft., A conclusion was reached that the object was not a balloon or satellite., The object was noted to be observed between the pointers in Ursa Minor.
sighted object: planet-like object of first magnitude brilliance
